-- U.K. Currency Trading Fell 3% in October From April to $1.97 Trillion/Day
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2012-02-06T14:08:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/u-k-currency-trading-fell-3-in-october-from-april-to-1-97-trillion-day.html
Foreign-exchange trading in the
U.K. fell 3 percent to $1.97 trillion a day in October compared
with April, according to a semi-annual survey of trading
published by the Foreign Exchange Joint Standing Committee.  From a year earlier, average daily trading was up 17
percent in October, according to the survey, published on the
Bank of England’s  website  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
